title: Local News: Popular Kalenjin Singer Diana Chelele recovering after attempting suicide
text:
By Wesley Kipng'enoh Tuesday, Oct 6th 2015 at 11:08 Chelele when she was admitted to the hospital 
By Wesley kipng'enoh (@Wess_kipp) 
Renowned Kalenjin singer Diana Chelele was admitted to Nakuru General Hospital on Saturday after an attempted suicide. 
The singer was reportedly found unconscious in a hotel in Nakuru after she informed her friends of her actions. 
She had travelled from Eldoret earlier on the day after a thrilling performance and was scheduled to perform in Kitengela over the weekend. 
According to sources close to her, Chelele's motive to commit suicide was marriage and legal woes that have been trailing her for the past few months. 
The “Pusurability” singer has had a controversial love life with her marriage reportedly on the rocks. In 2012 she was arraigned in court after being linked to death of an Eldoret surveyor but was later released. Chelele after performing in Eldoret 
Chelele was discharged from Nakuru General Hospital on Sunday eveningand is in her her rural home in Kapkwen, Bomet where she is currently recovering. 
She has released numerous Kalenjin hit song among them Chelele Binti Osama, Wrong number, Elifut among other songs. JOIN THE CONVERSATION
